<br>
The USA has no dependency on middle eastern oil whatsoever. The USA imports roughly 10 percent of its oil from the middle east, not exactly a crippling amount if were no longer available. However, the USA's buddies in NATO are very dependent on middle east oil. England, Germany, France, and especially Japan would be in dire straits without it. That is why the USA is so concerned with the oil. And if the USA asks for their help solving any problem associated with the flow of oil from the middle east, I seriously doubt any would dare refuse. You may remember Operation Desert Storm, the first three countries wanted to make damn sure they were represented in the press for sending military aid, and since Japan has been relegated to a purely defensive military force since WWII, and they wanted to be represented, they provided financial aid.<br>
<br>
I think Israel is well within their right to venture into Palestine and take whatever action they deem necessary to prevent/deter future terrorist action against their country. The sad fact of the matter is that whether you like it or not, it is war, people die in wars. If the Palestinians are such cowards that the cell leaders of their terrorists organizations only travel in the open with women and children close to them as human shields in the hope that that will stay the hand of the IDF, then the IDF is forced to the very difficult decision of taking a target of opportunity regardless of the collateral damage. That sucks, but like I said, its war, people die.<br>
<br>
Basically there are three primary views on what is happenning in the Palestine/ Israeli war:<br>
<br>
1. The Israeli's are evil oppressors and deserve what they get.<br>
<br>
2. Both sides are at fault.<br>
<br>
3. The Palestinians are evil terrorists and bent on the destruction of Israel.<br>
<br>
The majority opinion here seems to be number 2 with tendencies to number 3.<br>
<br>
<br>
So lets look at some possible solutions to these problems.<br>
<br>
If you think number 1 is the problem, have the USA invade Israel and Palestine simultaneously and completely disarm them both, stop all sales of military equipment to Israel. Leave and let them throw rocks at each other. Consequences: 30,000 Americans dead from the invasion. No future middle east blood on American hands. Israel gets whacked by Egypt, UN dissolves.<br>
<br>
If you think 2 is the problem. Step up weapons production in the USA, sell to both sides at cost, and let them commit genocide on each other. Consequences: an insignificant decrease in unemployment for a few years in the USA.<br>
<br>
If you think 3 is the problem. Evacuate all the Jews out of Israel and set them up in Utah. Give all of Israel to Palestine.<br>
Wait a month or 2 for the Palestinians to move into Tel Aviv, then send in about 10 waves of B2 bombers with daisy cutters and commit genocide on the Palestinians. Consequences: WWIII<br>
<br>
Obviously these are all oversimplified solutions, and none will ever happen. Although I do think solution 3 is deliciously evil  I really wouldnt personally endorse it.<br>
<br>
What I think will happen, is the USA will tell Israel to get out of Palestine or lose all military aid. Israel will back down. Then the USA will give them billions of dollars for anti-terrorist financial aid.<br>
<br>
And the cycle of violence will continue as it has for the last few millennia.<br>
<br>
My 2 cents<br>
<br>
Falconfist Flyingfury - Tunare<br>
<br>
